# These checksums are used by remote projects to validate that their locally
# synced copies of agent files have not been modified since they were fetched.
#
# Usage:
#   cd your-project-root
#   sha256sum --check .github/agents/CHECKSUMS.sha256
#
# To update checksums after changes to this repo, run:
#   cd /path/to/AgentInstructions
#   bash setup-agents.sh --update-checksums
#
# Remote projects that sync these files should copy this file alongside the
# agent files into their own .github/agents/ directory.

